No account creation is required.
No in-app purchases or subscriptions are present.
User-created scans, report drafts, attachments, optional profile details, and app settings are stored locally on device using SwiftData.
Camera permission is used only for live scanning of shelf labels, packaging text, and date codes.
Location permission is optional and used only to tag scans and support nearby warned-store features.
Photo library access is optional and used only when the user chooses evidence images or chooses to save evidence photos back to Photos.
Notifications are optional and used only for reminders and alerts.
The app may fetch public food recall data from openFDA. User scan contents are not uploaded as part of recall sync.
